  "label": "Cinderwall Sleep Niche",
  "description": "This compact bedroom is built as a deep-set niche within the Cinderwall Hab Suite, its basalt ribs and slagcrete panels overlaid with ashproof seals. A low bunk platform and wall-fastened storage lockers keep the floor clear, while a curtained sleeping recess breaks the violet-tinged spill from the suite’s shielded lighting. Gasketed shutters and a baffled vent-grille reduce infiltration to a fine soot film along the plascrete skirting. Vitrified patches on the inner wall catch stormlight as hard, glassy reflections, lending the space a permanent bruise-colored cast.",
